\begin_body

\begin_layout Chapter
\start_of_appendix
χ2 test of the model calculation for the Low-Mass dielectron spectra
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to quantify how different model compare with the measured data
 in Fig 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:excess-1"

\end_inset

, a χ2 test are performed.
 but in our measured data, the total uncertainty contain three part: (1)statisti
cal uncertainty, (2)systematic uncertainty and (3)the cocktail uncertainty.
 Here the uncertainty(1) are independent for each data point, uncertainty(2)
 and (3) are correlated for each data point, so we used a new χ2 calculation
 method 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "PhysRevC.77.064907"

\end_inset

, which list below: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\chi^{2}=\sum_{i=1}^{n}\frac{[y_{i}+\varepsilon_{b}\sigma_{b_{i}}-\mu_{i}(\vec{p})]^{2}}{\widetilde{\sigma}_{i}^{2}}+\varepsilon_{b}^{2}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the measured data point, 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{i}$
\end_inset

 are independent uncertainty, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{i}$
\end_inset

 are the model value.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{b_{i}}$
\end_inset

 are the correlated uncertainty,
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{b}$
\end_inset

 are the fraction variation of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{b_{i}}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\widetilde{\sigma}_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the uncertainty scaled by the multiplicative shift in 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}$
\end_inset

 such that the fractional uncertainty is unchanged under shifts.
 In our calculation, the statistical uncertainty are consider as independent
 for each data point, systematic uncertainty and cocktail uncertainty are
 consider as the correlated uncertainty, which is defined following:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\widetilde{\sigma}_{i}=\sigma_{i}(\frac{y_{i}+\varepsilon_{b}\sigma_{b_{i}}}{y_{i}})
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

